    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "This is a double-hop issue, I think. When in a remote session you can't use implicit credentials to access another machine remotely. You need to provide explicit credentials. I'm not super familiar how that's done in .NET, but in PS you would define a new PSDrive with `New-PSDrive` pointing to the remote host and supply a `-Credential` to authenticate.\r\n\r\nThis is a Windows remoting limitation, not something intrinsic to PowerShell, as far as I understand.",
